{"id":"260026742_The_logical_encoding_of_Sugeno_integrals","abstract":"Sugeno integrals are a well-known family of qualitative multiple criteria aggregation operators. The paper investigates how the behavior of these operators can be described in a prioritized propositional logic language, namely possibilistic logic. The case of binary-valued criteria, which amounts to providing a logical description of the fuzzy measure underlying the integral, is first considered. The general case of a Sugeno integral when critersia are valued on a discrete scale is then studied. (c) 2014 Elsevier B.V. All rights reserved.","authors":["Didier Dubois","Henri Prade","Rico Agnes"],"meta":["April 2014Fuzzy Sets and Systems 241","DOI:10.1016/j.fss.2013.12.014"],"references":["268199310_Stable_Models_in_Generalized_Possibilistic_Logic","220814901_Ranking_Alternatives_on_the_Basis_of_Generic_Constraints_and_Examples_-_A_Possibilistic_Approach","220444895_Using_Possibilistic_Logic_for_Modeling_Qualitative_Decision_ATMS-based_Algorithms","220354421_The_Use_of_the_Discrete_Sugeno_Integral_in_Decision-Making_A_Survey","23530714_A_Decade_of_Application_of_the_Choquet_and_Sugeno_Integrals_in_Multi-criteria_Decision_Aid","313059750_Theory_of_capacities","285812425_K-order_Pan-discrete_fuzzy_measures","271362495_The_Use_of_the_Discrete_Sugeno_Integral_in_Decision-Making_A_Survery","268315697_Qualitative_Possibility_Functions_and_Integrals","266293974_Possibility_Theory_Qualitative_and_Quantitative_Aspects","265461565_Theory_of_Capacities","239667554_Aggregation_operators_for_multicriteria_decision_aid","239662875_Fuzzy_measures_and_fuzzy_integrals_A_survey","229913006_A_Mathematical_Theory_of_Evidence","226927397_A_Possibilistic_Logic_View_of_Sugeno_Integrals","225070185_A_Mathematical_Theory_of_Evidence","223404852_Logical_representation_and_fusion_of_prioritized_information_based_on_guaranteed_possibility_measures_Application_to_the_distance-based_merging_of_classical_bases","222572108_The_Mob